%pyspark

from urllib2 import urlopen
import pandas as pd
import re, os

def airbnburlminer(country='singapore', dataset='listings', ext='.csv.gz'):
    page = urlopen('http://insideairbnb.com/get-the-data.html')
    html = page.read().decode("utf-8")
    urlarr = [str(re.sub('<a href=".*?', "", csvfile)).replace('"','') for csvfile in re.findall('<a href=".*{}.*?{}{}"'.format(country,dataset,ext), html)]
    print('\n'.join(urlarr))
    return pd.concat(map(lambda file: pd.read_csv(file, low_memory=False), urlarr))
    
#mining insiderairbnb page 
df = airbnburlminer()
df = df.drop_duplicates()
#remove any duplicate rows

%pyspark
# Data cleaning / remove null values
nulldf = pd.isnull(df).sum()/len(df)
nulldf = pd.DataFrame(nulldf.sort_values(ascending=False),columns=["null_values"])
reviewarr = [col for col in df.columns.tolist() if "review_scores" in col]
nullcol = [col for col in nulldf[nulldf['null_values'] > 0].index.tolist() if col not in ['beds','bathrooms','bedrooms']+reviewarr]
airbnbdf = df.drop(axis=1, columns=nullcol)
airbnbdf = airbnbdf.dropna(how='any',axis=0)
airbnbdf = airbnbdf.fillna(0,axis=1)

%pyspark
# Generate CSV file for other app
del df, nulldf
airbnbdf.info()
airbnbdf.to_csv(os.path.join(z.get('WORKPATH'),z.get('BIGCSV')), index=False)
